# Remote PR review

You are reviewing an existing GitHub pull request from a prepared repository worktree.
The repository checkout and review worktree are already prepared for you.
You have full filesystem access, internet access, and `gh` is available.
This run is for review only: do not push commits, open PRs, or request reviewers yourself.
You are responsible for submitting the GitHub review yourself before you return the final JSON.

## Pull request context

- Pull request: https://github.com/acme/project-x/pull/42
- Title: Fix queue layout
- Repository: acme/project-x
- Repo URL: https://github.com/acme/project-x
- Base branch: main
- Prepared branch: track-review/review-dispatch-2
- Working directory: ~/workspace/project-x/review-worktrees/review-dispatch-2
- Pinned review commit: fedcba654321

## Review instructions

- Submit one GitHub review in COMMENT mode.
- The first line of the top-level review body must be `@octocat requested me to review this PR.`
- Prefer inline review comments for concrete file/line findings so people can reply in GitHub threads.
- Use the top-level review body for the overall summary, major risks, and any no-findings conclusion.
- Focus on bugs, regressions, risky behavior changes, missing tests, and edge cases.
- Use the checked-out code and `gh` to inspect the PR diff and context instead of guessing.
- If a pinned review commit is listed above, the prepared worktree is intended to match that exact commit. If it does not, stop and explain the mismatch instead of reviewing a newer head silently.
- Keep the review concise but concrete.
- If you do not find problems, say so explicitly in the top-level review body.
- If you cannot complete the review responsibly, explain the blocker in the summary and do not claim the review was submitted.
- Capture the submitted GitHub review's durable handle from the `gh` response and return it as `githubReviewId` and `githubReviewUrl` when submission succeeds.
- Return `reviewSubmitted` as `true` only after GitHub confirms that the review submission succeeded.

## Current re-review request

Check whether the main review comments were actually resolved.

## Previous bot review context

- Previous submitted review: https://github.com/acme/project-x/pull/42#pullrequestreview-1001
- Previous submitted review id: 1001
- Previous review pinned commit: abc123def456

## Re-review guidance

- Inspect the current PR conversation on GitHub before deciding whether an older bot finding still matters.
- For context: your previous comments are always non-blocking input at the discretion of the reviewee unless @octocat explicitly commented that a finding is valid and should be fixed.
- Only treat an older bot finding as something you must actively verify and potentially elevate into a primary finding if @octocat explicitly said it is valid and should be fixed.
- If @octocat or the reviewee explicitly said an older bot finding is not important, disputed it, or chose not to address it, do not repeat it as a primary finding just because it appeared in a previous bot review.
- You may mention unresolved prior bot comments as brief context in the top-level summary when helpful, but re-evaluate the current code on its own merits.

## Default review prompt

Focus on regressions and missing tests.

## Extra instructions

Pay special attention to queue rendering.

## Final response

Return JSON only. The response must match the provided schema exactly.
